\[r = \frac{12 - x}{2 \sin \theta} = \frac{x}{2 \cos \theta}.\]Hence,
\[V = \frac{1}{3} \cdot \pi r^2 \cdot HG = \frac{1}{3} \cdot \pi \cdot \frac{x^2}{4 \cos^2 \theta} \cdot (12 - x).\]We want to minimize $V$ subject to $0 < x < 12.$  Since $\cos^2 \theta = 1 - \sin^2 \theta,$ we can write
\[V = \frac{1}{3} \cdot \pi \cdot \frac{x^2}{4 (1 - \sin^2 \theta)} \cdot (12 - x).\]Thus, we want to minimize
\[\frac{x^2 (12 - x)}{12 - x + 4 \sin^2 \theta x^2}.\]Since $0 < x < 12,$ $0 < \sin^2 \theta \le 1,$ and
\begin{align*}
\frac{x^2 (12 - x)}{12 - x + 4 \sin^2 \theta x^2} &\ge \frac{x^2 (12 - x)}{12 - x + 4x^2} \\
&= \frac{x^2 (12 - x)}{(2x - 3)(2x + 4)} \\
